    <h1>Space Race</h1>

    <p>
        The heated competition between the US and the USSR to be the first in space was a defining component of the Cold War. The Space Race illustrates exactly what humanity can accomplish when it sets its mind to work.
    </p>
    <p>
        After working for a little over a decade, the United States was able to successfully execute a crewed lunar landing, all while using technology that, compared to today’s standards, was severely limited. The motivator for this accomplishment was Soviet competition. The resulting struggle on both sides for better equipment, engineers, and research pushed the envelope of technological advancement.
    </p>

